    var originalOnError = window.onerror || function () {};
    var JS_SCRIPT_ERROR = 'Script error.';
    var SCRIPT_ERROR_COUNTER = 's-script-error';

    window.onerror = function onerror (message, file, line, col, error) {
        // Since "Script error." is what browsers send to the onerror callback when an error originates from a JavaScript
        // file served from a different origin, it doesn't have any actionable data. Hence log a counter instead of letting

        if(message === JS_SCRIPT_ERROR && ue && ue.count) {
            ue.count(SCRIPT_ERROR_COUNTER, (ue.count(SCRIPT_ERROR_COUNTER) || 0) + 1);
            return;
        }

        originalOnError(message, file, line, col, error);
    };
